Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into roughly 2cm chunks (no need to peel) and pop onto a large, low-sided, wide #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, then season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and the @dried oregano{1}(dried). Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potato chunks nicely spread out.

Put the @peri peri seasoning{1}, garlic and half of the @honey{15%ml} into a large #bowl{}. Drizzle in some oil, season with salt and pepper and mix to combine into a paste. Add the @British chicken breasts{2} and turn to coat in the paste, then pop onto another baking tray.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling chicken and its packaging.

When the oven is hot, roast the potato chunks on the top shelf and the chicken on the middle shelf until golden and cooked through, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

In another large bowl, add the @cider vinegar{15%ml}, @olive oil{1%tbsp}(for the dressing) and remaining honey. Season with salt and pepper, mix well then set aside. This is your salad dressing.

While everything cooks, chill out! Just before serving, add the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g} and @pea shoots{40%g} to the dressing bowl and toss well to coat.

> TIP: Keep a portion of salad aside before dressing, in case anyone prefers it plain.

When everything is ready, divide the potato chunks between your plates. Serve the chicken and pea shoot salad alongside, with a dollop of @mayonnaise{1%tbsp} for dipping. Enjoy!